f10BgpM2.name: f10BgpM2

revisions.description: This is a Force10 proprietary vesrion of the draft-ietf-idr-bgp4-mibv2-05.txt MIB as proposed by the IETF Inter-Domain Routing Working Group. This mib will be obsolete when IANA-number is assigned. The following objects are added by Force10. - Added to BgpM2PeerCounterstable f10BgpM2PeerInKeepalives, f10BgpM2PeerOutKeepalives, f10BgpM2PeerInOpen, f10BgpM2PeerOutOpen, f10BgpM2PeerInRteRefresh, f10BgpM2PeerOutRteRefresh - Added to BgpM2PrefixCountersTable f10BgpM2PrefixWdrawnByPeer, f10BgpM2PrefixWdrawnFromPeer

f10BgpM2.description: This MIB module defines management objects for the Border Gateway Protocol, Version 4.

F10BgpM2Identifier.name: F10BgpM2Identifier
F10BgpM2Identifier.description: The representation of a BGP Identifier. The BGP Identifier should be represented in the OCTET STRING as with the first OCTET of the string containing the first OCTET of the BGP Identifier received or sent in the OPEN packet and so on. Even though the BGP Identifier is trending away from an IP address it is still displayed as if it was one, even when it would be an illegal IP address.

F10BgpM2Afi.name: F10BgpM2Afi
F10BgpM2Afi.description: The representation of a BGP AFI

F10BgpM2Safi.name: F10BgpM2Safi
F10BgpM2Safi.description: The representation of a BGP SAFI

F10BgpM2Community.name: F10BgpM2Community
F10BgpM2Community.description: The representation of a BGP Community.

F10BgpM2ExtendedCommunity.name: F10BgpM2ExtendedCommunity
F10BgpM2ExtendedCommunity.description: The representation of a BGP Extended Community.

f10BgpM2Established.name: f10BgpM2Established
f10BgpM2Established.description: The BGP Established event is generated when the BGP FSM enters the ESTABLISHED state.

f10BgpM2BackwardTransition.name: f10BgpM2BackwardTransition
f10BgpM2BackwardTransition.description: The BGPBackwardTransition Event is generated when the BGP FSM moves from a higher numbered state to a lower numbered state.

f10BgpM2VersionEntry.name: f10BgpM2VersionEntry
f10BgpM2VersionEntry.description: Entry containing data on a given supported version of the Border Gateway Protocol and the level of support provided. It is expected that any agent implementation supporting this MIB module will report support for Version 4 of the Border Gateway Protocol at the very minimum.

f10BgpM2VersionIndex.name: f10BgpM2VersionIndex
f10BgpM2VersionIndex.description: The version number of the BGP Protocol.

f10BgpM2VersionSupported.name: f10BgpM2VersionSupported
f10BgpM2VersionSupported.description: This value is TRUE if this version of the BGP protocol identified in 'f10BgpM2VersionIndex' is supported. The absence of a row for a particular f10BgpM2VersionIndex indicates that that f10BgpM2VersionIndex protocol version number is not supported.

f10BgpM2CapabilitySupportAvailable.name: f10BgpM2CapabilitySupportAvailable
f10BgpM2CapabilitySupportAvailable.description: This value is TRUE if capability support is available and is enabled.

f10BgpM2SupportedCapabilitiesEntry.name: f10BgpM2SupportedCapabilitiesEntry
f10BgpM2SupportedCapabilitiesEntry.description: Information about supported capabilities indexed by capability number.

f10BgpM2SupportedCapabilityCode.name: f10BgpM2SupportedCapabilityCode
f10BgpM2SupportedCapabilityCode.description: Index of supported capability. The index directly corresponds with the BGP-4 Capability Advertisement Capability Code.

f10BgpM2SupportedCapability.name: f10BgpM2SupportedCapability
f10BgpM2SupportedCapability.description: This value is True if this capability is supported, False otherwise.

f10BgpM2AsSize.name: f10BgpM2AsSize
f10BgpM2AsSize.description: The size of the AS value in this implementation. The semantics of this are determined as per the as-4bytes draft.

f10BgpM2LocalAs.name: f10BgpM2LocalAs
f10BgpM2LocalAs.description: The local autonomous system number. If the f10BgpM2AsSize is twoOctet, then the range is constrained to be 0-65535.

f10BgpM2LocalIdentifier.name: f10BgpM2LocalIdentifier
f10BgpM2LocalIdentifier.description: The BGP Identifier of local system. Current practice is trending away from this value being treated as an IP address and more as a generic identifier.

f10BgpM2RouteReflector.name: f10BgpM2RouteReflector
f10BgpM2RouteReflector.description: This value is TRUE if this implementation supports the BGP Route Reflection Extension and is enabled as a route reflector. If the BGP Route Reflection extension is not supported this value must be FALSE.

f10BgpM2ClusterId.name: f10BgpM2ClusterId
f10BgpM2ClusterId.description: The configured Cluster-ID of the BGP Speaker. This will default to the BGP Speaker's F10BgpM2Identifier if this speaker is functioning as a route reflector and an explicit Cluster-ID has not been configured. A value of 0.0.0.0 will be present if Route Reflection is not enabled.

f10BgpM2ConfederationRouter.name: f10BgpM2ConfederationRouter
f10BgpM2ConfederationRouter.reference: RFC 3065 - Autonomous System Confederations for BGP
f10BgpM2ConfederationRouter.description: This value is TRUE if this implementation supports the BGP AS Confederations Extension and this router is configured to be in a confederation.

f10BgpM2ConfederationId.name: f10BgpM2ConfederationId
f10BgpM2ConfederationId.reference: RFC 3065 - Autonomous System Confederations for BGP
f10BgpM2ConfederationId.description: The local Confederation Identification Number. This value will be zero (0) if this BGP Speaker is not a confederation router.

f10BgpM2CfgBaseScalarStorageType.name: f10BgpM2CfgBaseScalarStorageType
f10BgpM2CfgBaseScalarStorageType.description: This object specifies the intended storage type for all configurable base scalars.

f10BgpM2CfgLocalAs.name: f10BgpM2CfgLocalAs
f10BgpM2CfgLocalAs.description: The local autonomous system number. If the f10BgpM2AsSize is twoOctet, then the range is constrained to be 0-65535.

f10BgpM2CfgLocalIdentifier.name: f10BgpM2CfgLocalIdentifier
f10BgpM2CfgLocalIdentifier.description: The BGP Identifier of local system. Current practice is trending away from this value being treated as an IP address and more as a generic identifier.

f10BgpM2CfgRouteReflector.name: f10BgpM2CfgRouteReflector
f10BgpM2CfgRouteReflector.description: This value is set to true if this implementation will be supporting route reflection.

f10BgpM2CfgClusterId.name: f10BgpM2CfgClusterId
f10BgpM2CfgClusterId.description: The configured Cluster-ID of the BGP Speaker. This will default to the BGP Speaker's F10BgpM2Identifier if this speaker is functioning as a route reflector and an explicit Cluster-ID has not been configured. A value of 0.0.0.0 will be present if Route Reflection is not enabled.

f10BgpM2CfgConfederationRouter.name: f10BgpM2CfgConfederationRouter
f10BgpM2CfgConfederationRouter.reference: RFC 3065 - Autonomous System Confederations for BGP
f10BgpM2CfgConfederationRouter.description: This value is set to true if this implementation will be supporting BGP AS Confederations.

f10BgpM2CfgConfederationId.name: f10BgpM2CfgConfederationId
f10BgpM2CfgConfederationId.reference: RFC 3065 - Autonomous System Confederations for BGP
f10BgpM2CfgConfederationId.description: The local Confederation Identification Number. This value will be zero (0) if this BGP Speaker is not a confederation router.

f10BgpM2PeerTable.name: f10BgpM2PeerTable
f10BgpM2PeerTable.description: BGP peer table. This table contains, one entry per remote BGP peer, any information about the connections with the remote BGP peers.

f10BgpM2PeerEntry.name: f10BgpM2PeerEntry
f10BgpM2PeerEntry.description: Entry containing information about the connection with a remote BGP peer.

f10BgpM2PeerInstance.name: f10BgpM2PeerInstance
f10BgpM2PeerInstance.description: The routing instance index. Some BGP implementations permit the creation of multiple instances of a BGP routing process. An example includes RFC 2547 PE-CE routers. Implementations that do not support multiple routing instances should return 1 for this object. XXX TODO - We need to provide a way to configure these in the peer configuration table.

f10BgpM2PeerIdentifier.name: f10BgpM2PeerIdentifier
f10BgpM2PeerIdentifier.description: The BGP Identifier of this entry's remote BGP peer. This entry should be 0.0.0.0 unless the f10BgpM2PeerState is in the OpenConfirm or the Established state.

f10BgpM2PeerState.name: f10BgpM2PeerState
f10BgpM2PeerState.description: The remote BGP peer's FSM state.

f10BgpM2PeerStatus.name: f10BgpM2PeerStatus
f10BgpM2PeerStatus.description: Whether or not the BGP FSM for this remote peer is halted or running. The BGP FSM for a remote peer is halted after processing a Stop event. Likewise, it is in the running state after a Start event. The f10BgpM2PeerState will generally be in the idle state when the FSM is halted, although some extensions such as Graceful Restart will leave the peer in the Idle state but with the FSM running.

f10BgpM2PeerConfiguredVersion.name: f10BgpM2PeerConfiguredVersion
f10BgpM2PeerConfiguredVersion.description: The configured version to originally start with this remote peer. The BGP speaker may permit negotiation to a lower version number of the protocol.

f10BgpM2PeerNegotiatedVersion.name: f10BgpM2PeerNegotiatedVersion
f10BgpM2PeerNegotiatedVersion.description: The negotiated version of BGP running between the two peers.

f10BgpM2PeerLocalAddrType.name: f10BgpM2PeerLocalAddrType
f10BgpM2PeerLocalAddrType.description: The address family of the local end of the peering session.

f10BgpM2PeerLocalAddr.name: f10BgpM2PeerLocalAddr
f10BgpM2PeerLocalAddr.description: The address of the local end of the peering session.

f10BgpM2PeerLocalPort.name: f10BgpM2PeerLocalPort
f10BgpM2PeerLocalPort.description: The local port for the TCP connection between the BGP peers.

f10BgpM2PeerLocalAs.name: f10BgpM2PeerLocalAs
f10BgpM2PeerLocalAs.description: Some implementations of BGP can represent themselves as multiple ASs. This is the AS that this peering session is representing itself as to the remote peer.

f10BgpM2PeerRemoteAddrType.name: f10BgpM2PeerRemoteAddrType
f10BgpM2PeerRemoteAddrType.description: The address family of the remote end of the peering session.

f10BgpM2PeerRemoteAddr.name: f10BgpM2PeerRemoteAddr
f10BgpM2PeerRemoteAddr.description: The address of the remote end of the peering session.

f10BgpM2PeerRemotePort.name: f10BgpM2PeerRemotePort
f10BgpM2PeerRemotePort.reference: RFC 2012 - SNMPv2 Management Information Base for the Transmission Control Protocol using SMIv2. RFC 2542 - IP Version 6 Management Information Base for the Transmission Control Protocol.
f10BgpM2PeerRemotePort.description: The remote port for the TCP connection between the BGP peers. In the case of a transport for which the notion of 'port' is irrelevant, an instance value of -1 should be returned by the agent for this object. Note that the objects f10BgpM2PeerLocalAddr, f10BgpM2PeerLocalPort, f10BgpM2PeerRemoteAddr and f10BgpM2PeerRemotePort provide the appropriate reference to the standard MIB TCP connection table. or even the ipv6 TCP MIB as in rfc2452.

f10BgpM2PeerIndex.name: f10BgpM2PeerIndex
f10BgpM2PeerIndex.description: This value is a unique index for the remote peer entry in the f10BgpM2PeerTable. It is assigned by the agent at the point of creation of the f10BgpM2PeerTable row entry. While its value is guaranteed to be unique at any time, it is otherwise opaque to the management application with respect to its value or the contiguity of f10BgpM2PeerIndex row instance values across rows of the f10BgpM2PeerTable. It is used to provide an index structure for other tables whose data is logically per-peer. For explicitly configured peers, this value will remain consistent until this row is deleted by deleting the configured peers. Unconfigured peers will generate a monotonically increasing number when a BGP FSM is built to process the peering session. Values in the f10BgpM2PeerTable and other tables utilizing f10BgpM2PeerIndex are expected to remain in existence for an arbitrary time after the unconfigured peer has been deleted in order to allow management applications to extract useful management information for those peers. Thus, an unconfigured peer using the same indices as the f10BgpM2PeerTable that comes up while this row still exists will re-utilize the same row.

f10BgpM2PeerErrorsTable.name: f10BgpM2PeerErrorsTable
f10BgpM2PeerErrorsTable.description: On a per peer basis, this table reflects the last protocol-defined error encountered and reported on the peer session. If no entry for a given peer, by its f10BgpM2PeerIndex, exists in this table, then no such errors have been observed, reported, and recorded on the session.

f10BgpM2PeerErrorsEntry.name: f10BgpM2PeerErrorsEntry
f10BgpM2PeerErrorsEntry.description: Each entry contains information about errors sent and received for a particular BGP peer.

f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceived.name: f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceived
f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceived.description: The last error code and subcode received by this BGP Speaker via a NOTIFICATION message for this peer. If no error has occurred, this field is zero. Otherwise, the first byte of this two byte OCTET STRING contains the error code, and the second byte contains the subcode.

f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSent.name: f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSent
f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSent.description: The last error code and subcode sent by this BGP Speaker via a NOTIFICATION message to this peer. If no error has occurred, this field is zero. Otherwise, the first byte of this two byte OCTET STRING contains the error code, and the second byte contains the subcode.

f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedTime.name: f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedTime
f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedTime.description: The timestamp that the last NOTIFICATION was received from this peer.

f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSentTime.name: f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSentTime
f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSentTime.description: The timestamp that the last NOTIFICATION was sent to this peer.

f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedText.name: f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedText
f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedText.description: This object contains an implementation specific explanation of the error that was reported.

f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSentText.name: f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSentText
f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSentText.description: This object contains an implementation specific explanation of the error that is being reported.

f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedData.name: f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedData
f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedData.description: The last error code's data seen by this peer.

f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSentData.name: f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSentData
f10BgpM2PeerLastErrorSentData.description: The last error code's data sent to this peer.

f10BgpM2PeerEventTimesTable.name: f10BgpM2PeerEventTimesTable
f10BgpM2PeerEventTimesTable.description: A table reporting the per-peering session amount of time elapsed and update events since the peering session advanced into the Established state.

f10BgpM2PeerEventTimesEntry.name: f10BgpM2PeerEventTimesEntry
f10BgpM2PeerEventTimesEntry.description: Each row contains a set of statistics about time spent and events encountered in the peer session Established state.

f10BgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTime.name: f10BgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTime
f10BgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTime.description: This timer indicates how long (in seconds) this peer has been in the Established state or how long since this peer was last in the Established state. It is set to zero when a new peer is configured or the router is booted.

f10BgpM2PeerInUpdatesElapsedTime.name: f10BgpM2PeerInUpdatesElapsedTime
f10BgpM2PeerInUpdatesElapsedTime.description: Elapsed time in seconds since the last BGP UPDATE message was received from the peer. Each time f10BgpM2PeerInUpdates is incremented, the value of this object is set to zero (0). This value shall also be zero (0) when the peer is not in the Established state

f10BgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersTable.name: f10BgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersTable
f10BgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersTable.description: Per peer management data on BGP session timers.

f10BgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersEntry.name: f10BgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersEntry
f10BgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to the current state of BGP timers on a given peering session.

f10BgpM2PeerConnectRetryInterval.name: f10BgpM2PeerConnectRetryInterval
f10BgpM2PeerConnectRetryInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the ConnectRetry timer. The suggested value for this timer is 120 seconds.

f10BgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured.name: f10BgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured
f10BgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Time configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. This value is placed in an OPEN message sent to this peer by this BGP speaker, and is compared with the Hold Time field in an OPEN message received from the peer when determining the Hold Time (f10BgpM2PeerHoldTime) with the peer. This value must not be less than three seconds if it is not zero (0) in which case the Hold Time is NOT to be established with the peer. The suggested value for this timer is 90 seconds.

f10BgpM2PeerKeepAliveConfigured.name: f10BgpM2PeerKeepAliveConfigured
f10BgpM2PeerKeepAliveConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. The value of this object will only determine the KEEPALIVE messages frequency relative to the value specified in f10BgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured; the actual time interval for the KEEPALIVE messages is indicated by f10BgpM2PeerKeepAlive. A reasonable maximum value for this timer would be configured to be one third of that of f10BgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), no periodical KEEPALIVE messages are sent to the peer after the BGP connection has been established. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

f10BgpM2PeerMinASOrigInterval.name: f10BgpM2PeerMinASOrigInterval
f10BgpM2PeerMinASOrigInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinASOriginationInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 15 seconds.

f10BgpM2PeerMinRouteAdverInterval.name: f10BgpM2PeerMinRouteAdverInterval
f10BgpM2PeerMinRouteAdverInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinRouteAdvertisementInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

f10BgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersTable.name: f10BgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersTable
f10BgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersTable.description: Current values of per-peer timers which can be dynamically set in the f10BgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersTable. Values reflected in this table are the current operational values, after negotiation from values derived from initial configuration or last set from f10BgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersTable row instances.

f10BgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersEntry.name: f10BgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersEntry
f10BgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersEntry.description: Each entry reflects a value of the currently operational, negotiated timers as reflected in the F10BgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersEntry.

f10BgpM2PeerHoldTime.name: f10BgpM2PeerHoldTime
f10BgpM2PeerHoldTime.description: The value of this object is calculated by this BGP Speaker as being; zero (0) - if this was the value sent by the peer and this value is permitted by this BGP Speaker. In this case, no keepalive messages are sent and the Hold Timer is not set. At least three (3). This value is the smaller of the value sent by this peer in the OPEN message and f10BgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured for this peer. This value is only defined when the peering session is in the Established state.

f10BgpM2PeerKeepAlive.name: f10BgpM2PeerKeepAlive
f10BgpM2PeerKeepAlive.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer established with the peer. The value of this object is calculated by this BGP speaker such that, when compared with f10BgpM2PeerHoldTime, it has the same proportion as what f10BgpM2PeerKeepAliveConfigured has when compared with f10BgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), it indicates that the KeepAlive timer has not been established with the peer, or, the value of f10BgpM2PeerKeepAliveConfigured is zero (0). This value is only defined when the peering session is in the Established state.

f10BgpM2PeerCapsAnnouncedTable.name: f10BgpM2PeerCapsAnnouncedTable
f10BgpM2PeerCapsAnnouncedTable.description: This table contains the capabilities that are supported for a given peer.

f10BgpM2PeerCapsAnnouncedEntry.name: f10BgpM2PeerCapsAnnouncedEntry
f10BgpM2PeerCapsAnnouncedEntry.description: These entries are keyed by a BGP-4 peer remote address and the BGP Capability Code

f10BgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedCode.name: f10BgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedCode
f10BgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedCode.description: The BGP Capability Advertisement Capability Code.

f10BgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedIndex.name: f10BgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedIndex
f10BgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedIndex.description: Multiple instances of a given capability may be sent bgp a BGP speaker. This variable is used to index them.

f10BgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedValue.name: f10BgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedValue
f10BgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedValue.description: The value of the announced capability.

f10BgpM2PeerCapsReceivedTable.name: f10BgpM2PeerCapsReceivedTable
f10BgpM2PeerCapsReceivedTable.description: This table contains the capabilities that are supported for a given peer.

f10BgpM2PeerCapsReceivedEntry.name: f10BgpM2PeerCapsReceivedEntry
f10BgpM2PeerCapsReceivedEntry.description: These entries are keyed by a BGP-4 peer remote address and the BGP Capability Code

f10BgpM2PeerCapReceivedCode.name: f10BgpM2PeerCapReceivedCode
f10BgpM2PeerCapReceivedCode.description: The BGP Capability Advertisement Capability Code.

f10BgpM2PeerCapReceivedIndex.name: f10BgpM2PeerCapReceivedIndex
f10BgpM2PeerCapReceivedIndex.description: Multiple instances of a given capability may be sent bgp a BGP speaker. This variable is used to index them.

f10BgpM2PeerCapReceivedValue.name: f10BgpM2PeerCapReceivedValue
f10BgpM2PeerCapReceivedValue.description: The value of the announced capability.

f10BgpM2PeerCountersTable.name: f10BgpM2PeerCountersTable
f10BgpM2PeerCountersTable.description: The counters associated with a BGP Peer.

f10BgpM2PeerCountersEntry.name: f10BgpM2PeerCountersEntry
f10BgpM2PeerCountersEntry.description: Each entry contains counters of message transmissions and FSM transitions for a given BGP Peering session.

f10BgpM2PeerInUpdates.name: f10BgpM2PeerInUpdates
f10BgpM2PeerInUpdates.description: The number of BGP UPDATE messages received on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero (0) when the connection is established.

f10BgpM2PeerOutUpdates.name: f10BgpM2PeerOutUpdates
f10BgpM2PeerOutUpdates.description: The number of BGP UPDATE messages transmitted on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero (0) when the connection is established.

f10BgpM2PeerInTotalMessages.name: f10BgpM2PeerInTotalMessages
f10BgpM2PeerInTotalMessages.description: The total number of messages received from the remote peer on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

f10BgpM2PeerOutTotalMessages.name: f10BgpM2PeerOutTotalMessages
f10BgpM2PeerOutTotalMessages.description: The total number of messages transmitted to the remote peer on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

f10BgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTrans.name: f10BgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTrans
f10BgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTrans.description: The total number of times the BGP FSM transitioned into the established state for this peer.

f10BgpM2PeerInKeepalives.name: f10BgpM2PeerInKeepalives
f10BgpM2PeerInKeepalives.description: The number of Keepalive messages received from a peer.Implemented by Force10.

f10BgpM2PeerOutKeepalives.name: f10BgpM2PeerOutKeepalives
f10BgpM2PeerOutKeepalives.description: The number of Keepalive messages sent to a peer. Implemented by Force10.

f10BgpM2PeerInOpen.name: f10BgpM2PeerInOpen
f10BgpM2PeerInOpen.description: The number of Open messages received from a peer. Implemented by Force10.

f10BgpM2PeerOutOpen.name: f10BgpM2PeerOutOpen
f10BgpM2PeerOutOpen.description: The number of Open messages sent to a peer. Implemented by Force10.

f10BgpM2PeerInRteRefresh.name: f10BgpM2PeerInRteRefresh
f10BgpM2PeerInRteRefresh.description: The number of Route Refresh messages received from a peer. Implemented by Force10.

f10BgpM2PeerOutRteRefresh.name: f10BgpM2PeerOutRteRefresh
f10BgpM2PeerOutRteRefresh.description: The number of Route Refresh messages sent to a peer. Implemented by Force10.

f10BgpM2PrefixCountersTable.name: f10BgpM2PrefixCountersTable
f10BgpM2PrefixCountersTable.description: Additional per-peer, per AFI SAFI counters for prefixes

f10BgpM2PrefixCountersEntry.name: f10BgpM2PrefixCountersEntry
f10BgpM2PrefixCountersEntry.description: Entry containing information about a bgp-peers prefix counters.

f10BgpM2PrefixCountersAfi.name: f10BgpM2PrefixCountersAfi
f10BgpM2PrefixCountersAfi.description: The AFI index of the per-peer, per prefix counters

f10BgpM2PrefixCountersSafi.name: f10BgpM2PrefixCountersSafi
f10BgpM2PrefixCountersSafi.description: The SAFI index of the per-peer, per prefix counters

f10BgpM2PrefixInPrefixes.name: f10BgpM2PrefixInPrefixes
f10BgpM2PrefixInPrefixes.description: The number of prefixes received from a peer and are stored in the Adj-Ribs-In for that peer.

f10BgpM2PrefixInPrefixesAccepted.name: f10BgpM2PrefixInPrefixesAccepted
f10BgpM2PrefixInPrefixesAccepted.description: The number of prefixes for a peer that are installed in the Adj-Ribs-In and are eligible to become active in the Loc-Rib.

f10BgpM2PrefixInPrefixesRejected.name: f10BgpM2PrefixInPrefixesRejected
f10BgpM2PrefixInPrefixesRejected.description: The number of prefixes for a peer that are installed in the Adj-Ribs-In and are NOT eligible to become active in the Loc-Rib.

f10BgpM2PrefixOutPrefixes.name: f10BgpM2PrefixOutPrefixes
f10BgpM2PrefixOutPrefixes.description: The number of prefixes for a peer that are installed in that peers Adj-Ribs-Out.

f10BgpM2PrefixWdrawnByPeer.name: f10BgpM2PrefixWdrawnByPeer
f10BgpM2PrefixWdrawnByPeer.description: The number of prefixes withdrawn by a peer. Implemened by Force10.

f10BgpM2PrefixWdrawnFromPeer.name: f10BgpM2PrefixWdrawnFromPeer
f10BgpM2PrefixWdrawnFromPeer.description: The number of prefixes withdrawn from a peer. Implemened by Force10.

f10BgpM2PeerReflectorClientTable.name: f10BgpM2PeerReflectorClientTable
f10BgpM2PeerReflectorClientTable.description: Table of route reflection client settings on a per-peer basis.

f10BgpM2PeerReflectorClientEntry.name: f10BgpM2PeerReflectorClientEntry
f10BgpM2PeerReflectorClientEntry.description: Entry containing data on a per-peer basis on whether the peer is configured as a route reflector client.

f10BgpM2PeerReflectorClient.name: f10BgpM2PeerReflectorClient
f10BgpM2PeerReflectorClient.description: This value indicates whether the given peer is a reflector client of this router, or not. A value of nonClient indicates that this peer is not a reflector client. A value of client indicates that this peer is a reflector client that is not fully meshed with other reflector clients. A value of meshedClient indicates that the peer is a reflector client and is fully meshed with all other reflector clients. This value must be nonClient (0) for BGP external peers.

f10BgpM2PeerConfedMemberTable.name: f10BgpM2PeerConfedMemberTable
f10BgpM2PeerConfedMemberTable.description: Table of confederation member settings on a per-peer basis.

f10BgpM2PeerConfedMemberEntry.name: f10BgpM2PeerConfedMemberEntry
f10BgpM2PeerConfedMemberEntry.description: Entry containing data on a per-peer basis on whether the peer is configured as a BGP confederation member.

f10BgpM2PeerConfedMember.name: f10BgpM2PeerConfedMember
f10BgpM2PeerConfedMember.description: This value indicates whether the given peer is in our confederation or not.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusTable.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusTable
f10BgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusTable.description: Table containing rows for administratively starting and stopping peering sessions.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusEntry.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusEntry
f10BgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusEntry.description: Entry containing row for administratively starting and stopping peers.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatus.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatus
f10BgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatus.description: This object allows the Manual Stop and Manual Start events to be sent to an activated peering session.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerNextIndex.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerNextIndex
f10BgpM2CfgPeerNextIndex.description: This object contains the next appropriate value to use as an index for creation of a row instance in in the f10BgpM2CfgPeerTable. If the number of available entries in the f10BgpM2CfgPeerTable is exhausted, a retrieval value of this object instance will return 0. A value of 0 may also be returned if the agent is otherwise incapable of f10BgpM2CfgPeerTable row creation at the time of f10BgpM2CfgPeerNextIndex retrieval.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerTable.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerTable
f10BgpM2CfgPeerTable.description: BGP configuration peer table. This table allows the configuration of the parameters for a session with a BGP peer. +++wayne provide description of how config should be done for a peer per table.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerEntry.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerEntry
f10BgpM2CfgPeerEntry.description: Entry containing information set up by a management entity to configure a connection with a BGP peer.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfiguredVersion.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfiguredVersion
f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfiguredVersion.description: The configured version to originally start with this peer. The BGP speaker may permit negotiation to a lower version number of the protocol depending on the set value of f10BgpM2CfgAllowVersionNegotiation.

f10BgpM2CfgAllowVersionNegotiation.name: f10BgpM2CfgAllowVersionNegotiation
f10BgpM2CfgAllowVersionNegotiation.description: If set to true, during session establishment with this peer, negotiation to a version lower than that specified in f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfiguredVersion will be allowed.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddrType.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddrType
f10BgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddrType.description: The address family of the speakers of this BGP session.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddr.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddr
f10BgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddr.description: The address of the local end of the peering session.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerLocalAs.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerLocalAs
f10BgpM2CfgPeerLocalAs.description: Autonomous system represented to peer on peering session initialization. Some implementations of BGP can represent themselves as multiple ASes. These implementations can set this to an alternate autonomous system. If this object is set to zero (0) at the point this row instance is set to active, then the implementation will initialize this session representing itself as the value of f10BgpM2CfgLocalAs.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddrType.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddrType
f10BgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddrType.description: The address family of the speakers of the remote BGP session.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddr.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddr
f10BgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddr.description: The address of the remote end (destination address of peer) for peering session.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAs.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAs
f10BgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAs.description: Autonomous system number of the remote peer.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerEntryStorageType.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerEntryStorageType
f10BgpM2CfgPeerEntryStorageType.description: This object type specifies the intended storage type for the f10BgpM2CfgPeerEntry row instance.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerError.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerError
f10BgpM2CfgPeerError.description: This value indicates the current error status of the row denoting the configured error status. If this row is still under creation (has not been activated f10BgpM2CfgPeerRowEntryStatus), then this instance will be set to not-activated (1). At the point that the row is activated, f10BgpM2CfgPeerError will reflect the error status of the row data itself. If there is another session already activated with the same local and remote addresses as denoted by {f10BgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddrType, f10BgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddr, f10BgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddr}, then the value of this will be set to err-duplicate-peering-session (2). If this row is associated with a peer session whose initialization has been attempted, the value will be set to activated (3) (and, f10BgpM2PeerCfgPeerEntry will be set to the row instance of the entry in the f10BgpM2PeerTable which reflects the state of the peering session). Note that this object only reflects the error as a function of the attempted activation of this row as containing data for a bgp peering session. The actual state of the session at the point of any protocol exchange or session state machine initiation is reflected in the f10BgpM2PeerTable row instance (as reflected through f10BgpM2CfgPeerPeerEntry) associated with this row instance.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerBgpPeerEntry.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerBgpPeerEntry
f10BgpM2CfgPeerBgpPeerEntry.description: Upon activation of the session data contained in this row instance, this object points to an instance of a row within the f10BgpM2PeerTable reflecting the session in its initializing or operational state. Retrieval of this column instance will always yield a value of {0.0} unless the session has successfully been activated (via f10BgpM2CfgPeerRowEntryStatus). Such row instances will always have a value of f10BgpM2CfgPeerError which is activated (3).

f10BgpM2CfgPeerRowEntryStatus.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerRowEntryStatus
f10BgpM2CfgPeerRowEntryStatus.description: This object type is used to control creation, activation, and deletion of this row instance.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerIndex.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerIndex
f10BgpM2CfgPeerIndex.description: Uniquely identifies an instance of a peer row, as an element of configuration.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerStatus.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerStatus
f10BgpM2CfgPeerStatus.description: This specifies the state of the peering session upon activation. If disabled, the FSM is in the halted state and no Automatic Start events are generated. If enabled, the FSM is in the running state and Automatic Start events may be generated.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerTimersTable.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerTimersTable
f10BgpM2CfgPeerTimersTable.description: Table for configuration of per-peer timers.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerConnectRetryInterval.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerConnectRetryInterval
f10BgpM2CfgPeerConnectRetryInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the ConnectRetry timer. The suggested value for this timer is 120 seconds.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerHoldTimeConfigured.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerHoldTimeConfigured
f10BgpM2CfgPeerHoldTimeConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Time configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. This value is placed in an OPEN message sent to this peer by this BGP speaker, and is compared with the Hold Time field in an OPEN message received from the peer when determining the Hold Time (f10BgpM2PeerHoldTime) with the peer. This value must not be less than three seconds if it is not zero (0) in which case the Hold Time is NOT to be established with the peer. The suggested value for this timer is 90 seconds.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerKeepAliveConfigured.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerKeepAliveConfigured
f10BgpM2CfgPeerKeepAliveConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. The value of this object will only determine the KEEPALIVE messages frequency relative to the value specified in f10BgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured; the actual time interval for the KEEPALIVE messages is indicated by f10BgpM2PeerKeepAlive. A reasonable maximum value for this timer would be configured to be one third of that of f10BgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), no periodical KEEPALIVE messages are sent to the peer after the BGP connection has been established. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerMinASOrigInterval.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerMinASOrigInterval
f10BgpM2CfgPeerMinASOrigInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinASOriginationInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 15 seconds.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerMinRouteAdverInter.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerMinRouteAdverInter
f10BgpM2CfgPeerMinRouteAdverInter.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinRouteAdvertisementInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientTable.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientTable
f10BgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientTable.description: Table of route reflection client settings on a per-peer basis.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientEntry.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientEntry
f10BgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientEntry.description: Entry containing data on a per-peer basis on whether the peer is configured as a route reflector client.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClient.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClient
f10BgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClient.description: This value indicates whether the given peer is a reflector client of this router, or not. A value of nonClient indicates that this peer is not a reflector client. A value of client indicates that this peer is a reflector client that is not fully meshed with other reflector clients. A value of meshedClient indicates that the peer is a reflector client and is fully meshed with all other reflector clients. This value must be nonClient (0) for BGP external peers.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberTable.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberTable
f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberTable.description: Table of confederation member settings on a per-peer basis.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberEntry.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberEntry
f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberEntry.description: Entry containing data on a per-peer basis on whether the peer is configured as a BGP confederation member.

f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfedMember.name: f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfedMember
f10BgpM2CfgPeerConfedMember.description: This value indicates whether the given peer is in our confederation or not.

f10BgpM2NlriTable.name: f10BgpM2NlriTable
f10BgpM2NlriTable.description: The BGP-4 Received Path Attribute Table contains information about paths to destination networks received from all BGP4 peers. Collectively, this represents the Adj-Ribs-In. The route where f10BgpM2NlriBest is TRUE represents, for this NLRI, the route that is installed in the LocRib from the Adj-Ribs-In.

f10BgpM2NlriEntry.name: f10BgpM2NlriEntry
f10BgpM2NlriEntry.description: Information about a path to a network.

f10BgpM2NlriIndex.name: f10BgpM2NlriIndex
f10BgpM2NlriIndex.reference: RFC 3107 - Carrying Label Information in BGP-4
f10BgpM2NlriIndex.description: This index allows for multiple instances of a base prefix for a certain AFI SAFI from a given peer. This is currently useful for two things: 1. Allowing for a peer in future implementations to send more than a single route instance. 2. Allow for extensions which extend the NLRI field to send the same prefix while utilizing other extension specific information. An example of this is RFC 3107 - Carrying MPLS labels in BGP.

f10BgpM2NlriAfi.name: f10BgpM2NlriAfi
f10BgpM2NlriAfi.description: The address family of the prefix for this NLRI.

f10BgpM2NlriSafi.name: f10BgpM2NlriSafi
f10BgpM2NlriSafi.description: The subsequent address family of the prefix for this NLRI

f10BgpM2NlriPrefixType.name: f10BgpM2NlriPrefixType
f10BgpM2NlriPrefixType.description: The type of the IP address prefix in the Network Layer Reachability Information field. The value of this object is derived from the appropriate value from the f10BgpM2NlriAfi field. Where an appropriate InetAddressType is not available, the value of the object must be unknown(0). XXX TODO - This seems like a hack.

f10BgpM2NlriPrefix.name: f10BgpM2NlriPrefix
f10BgpM2NlriPrefix.description: An IP address prefix in the Network Layer Reachability Information field. This object is an IP address containing the prefix with length specified by f10BgpM2PathAttrAddrPrefixLen. Any bits beyond the length specified by f10BgpM2PathAttrAddrPrefixLen are zeroed.

f10BgpM2NlriPrefixLen.name: f10BgpM2NlriPrefixLen
f10BgpM2NlriPrefixLen.description: Length in bits of the address prefix in the Network Layer Reachability Information field.

f10BgpM2NlriBest.name: f10BgpM2NlriBest
f10BgpM2NlriBest.description: An indication of whether or not this route was chosen as the best BGP4 route.

f10BgpM2NlriCalcLocalPref.name: f10BgpM2NlriCalcLocalPref
f10BgpM2NlriCalcLocalPref.description: The degree of preference calculated by the receiving BGP4 speaker for an advertised route.

f10BgpM2PathAttrIndex.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrIndex
f10BgpM2PathAttrIndex.description: This value is a unique index for the per-NLRI entry in the f10BgpM2PathAttrTable. It is assigned by the agent at the point of creation of the f10BgpM2PathAttrTable row entry. While its value is guaranteed to be unique at any time, it is otherwise opaque to the management application with respect to its value or the contiguity of f10BgpM2PathAttrIndex row instance values across rows of the f10BgpM2PeerAttrTable. It is used to provide an index structure for other tables whose data is logically per-peer, per-NLRI.

f10BgpM2NlriOpaqueType.name: f10BgpM2NlriOpaqueType
f10BgpM2NlriOpaqueType.reference: RFC 3107 - Carrying Label Information in BGP-4 draft-ietf-mpls-lsr-mib-08.txt
f10BgpM2NlriOpaqueType.description: This object enumerates the type of the row that is pointed to in the table row f10BgpM2NlriOpaquePointer instance, if f10BgpM2NlriOpaquePointer is in fact not a zero length. f10BgpM2NlriOpaqueType is necessary since the data referenced by f10BgpM2NlriOpaquePointer is opaque to BGP. For example, in the case of RFC 3107, the label stack that is pointed to may occur in the mplsLabelStackTable from the MPLS-LSR-MIB, and the instance value of f10BgpM2NlriOpaqueType would be bgpMplsLabelStack(1).

f10BgpM2NlriOpaquePointer.name: f10BgpM2NlriOpaquePointer
f10BgpM2NlriOpaquePointer.description: Pointer to a row that decomposes the data that is opaque to the BGP MIB but is sent in the NLRI. This RowPointer has zero (0) length data instance if f10BgpM2NlriOpaqueType is none.

f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutTable.name: f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutTable
f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutTable.description: This table contains on a per-peer basis one or more routes from the f10BgpM2NlriTable that have been placed in this peer's Adj-Ribs-Out.

f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutEntry.name: f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutEntry
f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutEntry.description: List of BGP routes that have been placed into a peer's Adj-Ribs-Out.

f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutIndex.name: f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutIndex
f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutIndex.description: Certain extensions to BGP permit multiple instance of a per afi, per safi prefix to be advertised to a peer. This object allows the enumeration of them.

f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutRoute.name: f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutRoute
f10BgpM2AdjRibsOutRoute.description: This object points to the route in the f10BgpM2NlriTable that corresponds to the entry in the peer's Adj-Rib-Out. Outgoing route maps are not reflected at this point as those are part of the Update-Send process.

f10BgpM2PathAttrCount.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrCount
f10BgpM2PathAttrCount.description: The number of entries in the f10BgpM2PathAttrTable.

f10BgpM2PathAttrTable.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrTable
f10BgpM2PathAttrTable.description: Provides per advertised network-prefix attribute data, as advertised over a peering session.

f10BgpM2PathAttrEntry.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrEntry
f10BgpM2PathAttrEntry.description: Each entry contains data about a given network prefix, per-prefix and per-advertising peer.

f10BgpM2PathAttrOrigin.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrOrigin
f10BgpM2PathAttrOrigin.description: The ultimate origin of the path information.

f10BgpM2PathAttrNextHopAddrType.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrNextHopAddrType
f10BgpM2PathAttrNextHopAddrType.description: The address family of the address for the border router that should be used to access the destination network.

f10BgpM2PathAttrNextHop.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrNextHop
f10BgpM2PathAttrNextHop.description: The address of the border router that should be used to access the destination network. This address is the nexthop address received in the UPDATE packet. The address family of this object will be the same as that of the prefix in this row. Note that for RFC2545 style double nexthops, this object will always contain the global scope nexthop. f10BgpM2LinkLocalNextHopTable will contain the linklocal scope nexthop. In the case that the mechanism documented in draft-kato-bgp-ipv6-link-local-00.txt is used and only a link local nexthop has been sent, , f10BgpM2LinkLocalNextHopPresent will be false and f10BgpM2PathAttrNextHop will contain the link local nexthop.

f10BgpM2PathAttrMedPresent.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrMedPresent
f10BgpM2PathAttrMedPresent.description: Whether or not the MED value is present. If it is not present, the f10BgpM2PathAttrMed object has no useful value and should be set to 0.

f10BgpM2PathAttrMed.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrMed
f10BgpM2PathAttrMed.description: This metric is used to discriminate between multiple exit points to an adjacent autonomous system.

f10BgpM2PathAttrLocalPrefPresent.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrLocalPrefPresent
f10BgpM2PathAttrLocalPrefPresent.description: Whether or not the LocalPref value is present. If it is not present, the f10BgpM2PathAttrLocalPref object has no useful value and should be set to 0.

f10BgpM2PathAttrLocalPref.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrLocalPref
f10BgpM2PathAttrLocalPref.description: The originating BGP4 speakers degree of preference for an advertised route.

f10BgpM2PathAttrAtomicAggregate.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrAtomicAggregate
f10BgpM2PathAttrAtomicAggregate.description: When this object is set to atomicAggregatePresent, the ATOMIC_AGGREGATE Path Attribute is present and indicates that the NLRI MUST NOT be made more specific.

f10BgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAS.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAS
f10BgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAS.description: The AS number of the last BGP4 speaker that performed route aggregation. A value of zero (0) indicates the absence of this attribute. Note propagation of AS of zero is illegal in the Internet.

f10BgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAddr.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAddr
f10BgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAddr.description: The IP address of the last BGP4 speaker that performed route aggregation. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates the absence of this attribute.

f10BgpM2AsPathCalcLength.name: f10BgpM2AsPathCalcLength
f10BgpM2AsPathCalcLength.description: This value represents the calculated length of the AS Path according to the rules of the BGP specification. This value is used in route selection.

f10BgpM2AsPathString.name: f10BgpM2AsPathString
f10BgpM2AsPathString.description: This is a string depicting the autonomous system path to this network which was received from the peer which advertised it. The format of the string is implementation-dependent, and should be designed for operator readability.

f10BgpM2AsPathIndex.name: f10BgpM2AsPathIndex
f10BgpM2AsPathIndex.description: This value is a unique index for the decomposed AS Path in the f10BgpM2AsPathTable. It is assigned by the agent at the point of creation of the f10BgpM2AsPathTable row entry. While its value is guaranteed to be unique at any time, it is otherwise opaque to the management application with respect to its value or the contiguity of f10BgpM2AsPathIndex row instance values across rows of the f10BgpM2AsPathTable.

f10BgpM2AsPath4byteTable.name: f10BgpM2AsPath4byteTable
f10BgpM2AsPath4byteTable.reference: draft-ietf-idr-as4bytes-04.txt - BGP support for four-octet AS number space
f10BgpM2AsPath4byteTable.description: This table is present for BGP speakers that support the AS 4byte specification and are functioning as a router between 2-byte and 4-byte AS space.

f10BgpM2AsPath4byteEntry.name: f10BgpM2AsPath4byteEntry
f10BgpM2AsPath4byteEntry.description: Each row contains the information for the AS 4-byte extension's NEW_AS_PATH and NEW_AGGREGATOR attributes.

f10BgpM2AsPath4bytePathPresent.name: f10BgpM2AsPath4bytePathPresent
f10BgpM2AsPath4bytePathPresent.description: This value may only be true if this BGP Speaker is functioning as a router between ASs that are in 2-byte and 4-byte AS space. If this value is true, then the NEW_AS_PATH attributes are present and the 4-byte versions of the appropriate path attributes are in this row. If this value is false, then the following values will be present in the row: f10BgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAS - zero (0). f10BgpM2AsPathCalcLength - zero (0). f10BgpM2AsPathString - zero (0) length string. f10BgpM2AsPathIndex - zero (0).

f10BgpM2AsPath4byteAggregatorAS.name: f10BgpM2AsPath4byteAggregatorAS
f10BgpM2AsPath4byteAggregatorAS.description: The NEW_AGGREGATOR AS number of the last BGP4 speaker that performed route aggregation. A value of zero (0) indicates the absence of this attribute. Note propagation of AS of zero is illegal in the Internet.

f10BgpM2AsPath4byteCalcLength.name: f10BgpM2AsPath4byteCalcLength
f10BgpM2AsPath4byteCalcLength.description: This value represents the calculated length of the NEW_AS_PATH according to the rules of the BGP specification. This value is used in route selection.

f10BgpM2AsPath4byteString.name: f10BgpM2AsPath4byteString
f10BgpM2AsPath4byteString.description: This is a string depicting the autonomous system path to this network which was received from the peer which advertised it. The format of the string is implementation-dependent, and should be designed for operator readability.

f10BgpM2AsPath4byteIndex.name: f10BgpM2AsPath4byteIndex
f10BgpM2AsPath4byteIndex.description: This value is a unique index for the decomposed AS Path in the f10BgpM2AsPathTable. It is assigned by the agent at the point of creation of the f10BgpM2AsPathTable row entry. While its value is guaranteed to be unique at any time, it is otherwise opaque to the management application with respect to its value or the contiguity of f10BgpM2AsPathIndex row instance values across rows of the f10BgpM2AsPathTable.

f10BgpM2AsPathTable.name: f10BgpM2AsPathTable
f10BgpM2AsPathTable.description: The BGP-4 Path Attribute AS Path Table contains the per network path (NLRI) AS PATH data received from the advertising BGP peer.

f10BgpM2AsPathTableEntry.name: f10BgpM2AsPathTableEntry
f10BgpM2AsPathTableEntry.description: Information about an AS path provided with a path to a network.

f10BgpM2AsPathSegmentIndex.name: f10BgpM2AsPathSegmentIndex
f10BgpM2AsPathSegmentIndex.description: A per-AS path segment index. This will index a set of autonomous systems in an AS path which are part of the same sequence or set (as determined by the row value of f10BgpM2AsPathType, which should be the same value for each f10BgpM2AsPathTable entry indexed by the same (f10BgpM2PathAttrIndex, f10BgpM2AsPathIndex) pair).

f10BgpM2AsPathElementIndex.name: f10BgpM2AsPathElementIndex
f10BgpM2AsPathElementIndex.description: A per-AS element index. This will index a particular AS within a sequence or set of autonomous systems in an AS path.

f10BgpM2AsPathType.name: f10BgpM2AsPathType
f10BgpM2AsPathType.description: The type of sequence in which this asPath was advertised as an attribute. Note that all asPath row instances for a given (f10BgpM2PathAttrIndex, f10BgpM2AsPathIndex) index pair will have their f10BgpM2AsPathType set to the same value. The values for f10BgpM2AsPathType are interpreted as defined in the base BGP document and the BGP AS Confederations document.

f10BgpM2AsPathElementValue.name: f10BgpM2AsPathElementValue
f10BgpM2AsPathElementValue.description: An AS value for an AS the related NLRI traversed in the propagation of its advertisement. This value is to be interpreted in the context of the sequence implied by f10BgpM2AsPathIndex and f10BgpM2AsPathType (and, in sequence of the other table rows with the same value of f10BgpM2PathAttrIndex and f10BgpM2AsPathIndex).

f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownTable.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownTable
f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownTable.description: The BGP-4 Path Attribute Unknown Table contains the per network path (NLRI) data on the path attributes advertised with a route but not known to the local BGP implementation or not otherwise capable of being returned from this agent. The absence of row data for a given index value for f10BgpM2PathAttrIndex indicates a lack of such unknown attribute information for the indicated network path (as indexed by that f10BgpM2PathAttrIndex value in the f10BgpM2PathAttrTable).

f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownEntry.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownEntry
f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownEntry.description: Information about an unknown attribute provided with a path to a network.

f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownIndex.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownIndex
f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownIndex.description: An integer index for a row in this table.

f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownType.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownType
f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownType.description: The attribute type advertised with this unknown attribute by the peer.

f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownValue.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownValue
f10BgpM2PathAttrUnknownValue.description: Value of path attribute not understood by the base BGP-4 document. Octets beyond the maximum size, if any, are not recorded by this row object.

f10BgpM2PathAttrOriginatorIdTable.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrOriginatorIdTable
f10BgpM2PathAttrOriginatorIdTable.description: Per prefix data pertinent to advertisement of a network prefix through an originator.

f10BgpM2PathAttrOriginatorIdEntry.name: f10BgpM2PathAttrOriginatorIdEntry
